Please answer the below Data Structure Questions:

Q. why do we need data structure?
A.
Data structure is important for storing, organizing and managing data so that we can access and modify it efficiently
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are the various operations that can be performed on different Data Structures?
A.
Searching in a data structure, insertion of data, deletion, selection, update, sort, split
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. List out the areas in which data structures are applied extensively?
A.
In Artificial Intelligence, numerical analysis, statistical analysis, database management system, compiler design
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is an Array?
A.
An array is a data structure in which we can store multiple values in a single variable.
In an array, the elements are indexed and the first element has the index 0.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between the Array and ArrayList?
A.
The difference between them is that Array's size can't be modified, if we want to add or remove elements
we have to create a new one, while in Arraylist we can add and remove elements as we want.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is LinkedList?
A.
LinkedList uses a doubly linked list to store items.  The elements are linked using pointers and addresses.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. How is an ArrayList different from Linked List?
A.
Arraylist has a regular list inside it and we can simply add elements into it, while in Linkedlist,
the elements are linked so if we want to add an element, this element is placed into an existing element
and an other one in the list (if it's in the middle).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between the HashTable and HashMap?
A.
A HashMap is not thread safe, while hashtable is thread safe and can be shared with multiple threads
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the major data structures used in the following areas : RDBMS, Network data model and Hierarchical data model?
A.
RDBMS: Array,
Network data model: Graph,
Hierarchical data model: Trees
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. How HashMap works in java?
A.
Hashmap stores data in the pair of key and value. It can contain different types of data.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in java? When it occurs?
A.
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException is a runtime exception. It occurs when an array is accessed with an illegal index.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the different ways of copying an array into another array?
A.

Create a new array of the same length and copy each element.
Using a variable assignment.
Using a method called clone which creates a new array of the same size.
Use System.arraycopy() method.
